WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-RU

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:02.950
Runic forms, inscriptions.

00:00:02.950 --> 00:00:05.800
This is the work of my whole life.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.350
The more I looked, the more I saw

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:11.350
similar shapes in the stars overhead.  It was then that

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.350
I dedicated myself to

00:00:15.916 --> 00:00:17.233
searching for runes.

00:00:18.550 --> 00:00:23.150
As Farrow kindly explained, runes
are very powerful and ancient inscriptions,

00:00:23.150 --> 00:00:26.350
and they can be embedded into objects
to imbue them with greater power.

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:30.300
During the league, glyphing relics will
allow you to choose

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.983
from a variety of different runes
to enhance your items.

00:00:34.633 --> 00:00:38.183
When you encounter a relic, it will have
several nests, ranging from two

00:00:38.733 --> 00:00:39.866
to seven.

00:00:39.866 --> 00:00:42.783
The more nests there are, the more difficult the battle at the relic is,

00:00:42.783 --> 00:00:45.450
but the more options you will have to choose from.

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:47.333
Early in the game, you can

00:00:47.333 --> 00:00:49.400
craft simple
damage or resistance runes

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:51.116
that are available at a
lower level

00:00:51.116 --> 00:00:52.616
than normal,

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.433
giving you a nice power boost.

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:56.516
But things quickly get more interesting.

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.233
There are 22 runes to add
or modify the runic barrier of a

00:01:00.483 --> 00:01:02.450
new resource that
can protect you from death.

00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:06.900
Using these runes, you can add an extra
layer of defense or transform your runic barrier

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:10.150
into an offensive weapon using
Kaluuran rune skills.

00:01:13.183 --> 00:01:16.600
There are also 13 runes that add
weapon-specific abilities,

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.833
such as this one that gives
grenades a second chance to explode.

00:01:21.283 --> 00:01:24.566
Or this one, which gives you a new
buff called Druidism

00:01:24.616 --> 00:01:26.200
when you heavily stun enemies.

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:29.850
Additionally,

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.850
there are 22 runes designed
to buff you at low levels,

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:35.850
like this one that gives
you a lot of elemental resistance,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.683
or this one that gives
you a lot of spirit.

00:01:38.683 --> 00:01:42.300
These runes are designed to be powerful,
but their value decreases as they level up.

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:45.300
They are great for quickly
leveling up the second character in the league.

00:01:45.733 --> 00:01:47.933
We also have six runes
that can be used

00:01:47.933 --> 00:01:51.016
to expand the property set
used in high-level crafting.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:55.133
For example, you can slot
Katla's Gloom into gloves, which will

00:01:55.133 --> 00:01:58.516
allow you to create a
variety of new decay properties

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.650
that can be used for
damage over time builds.

00:02:01.216 --> 00:02:03.316
After installing a rune of this type,

00:02:03.316 --> 00:02:06.416
use regular Exalted or Chaos Orbs
to try to gain new properties.

00:02:08.666 --> 00:02:10.583
There are also runes
that have one-time

00:02:10.583 --> 00:02:13.900
powerful effects on items
but are permanently bound to the socket,

00:02:14.066 --> 00:02:17.183
such as this one, which allows any
item to gain an additional suffix.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:23.516
Or this one, which allows you
to create a nest for a gem.

00:02:29.166 --> 00:02:30.400
Or this series of runes

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.566
that can transform any
elemental property from one element to another.

00:02:34.933 --> 00:02:37.700
There is even a rune that can
upgrade any other rune,

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:39.750
allowing them to be upgraded
beyond the normal limit.  The

00:02:42.133 --> 00:02:45.133
last rune I want to show
you today is Aldur's Legacy.  A

00:02:45.433 --> 00:02:50.266
special rune that can be installed into any Kalguuran or
Ezomyte unique item to destroy it,

00:02:50.266 --> 00:02:53.233
but in doing so, create a new rune that
inherits some of the unique item's properties.

00:02:53.816 --> 00:02:54.983
For example,

00:02:54.983 --> 00:02:58.350
use it on Flatfoot to
create the Flatfoot Heritage rune.

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.950
Equip it into any boot, and

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.683
like the unique item
it came from,

00:03:01.683 --> 00:03:05.233
you'll deal 10% overkill damage to
all enemies within two meters.

00:03:05.983 --> 00:03:08.700
How about Legacy of the Twisted Firmament?

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:10.466
Destroy the Twisted Firmament

00:03:10.466 --> 00:03:13.666
and you will be able to add Cold damage based on
your maximum Mana to any weapon.

00:03:14.783 --> 00:03:17.900
With Aldur's Legacy, you can
create about a hundred more runes

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.950
with all sorts of unique effects.

00:03:22.516 --> 00:03:25.116
At this point you might be thinking,
"That's a lot of new runes,"

00:03:25.116 --> 00:03:26.350
and you'd be right.

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:28.350
After all, these are the Runes of Aldur.

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.000
But we didn't want to leave the
old runes unattended.

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.700
A lot of old runes

00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:34.800
that weren't used
will also be improved,

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:37.233
which will greatly increase
the efficiency of the crafting system.

00:03:37.566 --> 00:03:39.183
Explore all the possibilities of runes

00:03:39.183 --> 00:03:42.883
in the Rise of the Ancients expansion,
coming May 29th.  See you!

